# Testing Conventions
- Use Vitest (`import { describe, it, expect, vi } from "vitest"`). Do NOT use Jest APIs.
- Use `@testing-library/react` (`render`, `screen`) and `@testing-library/user-event` for component tests.
- Place test files in `__tests__/` sibling directories (e.g. `components/__tests__/header.test.tsx`).
- Never use a real AI API key. Mock `@ai-sdk/google` and `@ai-sdk/react` with `vi.mock`.
- Mock `react-markdown` with a passthrough `<p>` in component tests that render markdown.
- Mock `sonner` (`toast`) in page-level tests.
- Run `npm test` after writing or modifying tests to verify they pass.
- See `TESTING_STRATEGY.md` for full strategy and mocking patterns.
